//Typedef:- typedef is used to create a new type name (alias) for an existing data type.
                 //The new type created by typedef is a user-defined type.
         // it's called as a user defined data type
// for example, If we have a data type definition that we want to reuse multiple times, we use typedef
//  other example:-if one class contains a handle of another class that is not yet defined, we use typedef . This is called a forward declaration.

  

module tab;
  typedef shortint a;
 
        a b;
       a  c;
  
     initial begin
       
     
//        a=6;  // it has not use
        b=8;
        c=9;
       $display("a=%0d b=%0d c=%0d",a,b,c);
     end
endmodule 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------ALIaS------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Alias means an alternative name for an existing entity. In typedef, an alias is a new name given to an existing data type.
alias creates an alternate name for an existing signal/net.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What does alias do?
alias makes two signals/nets refer to the same physical object.
They are effectively the same signal with two names.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Why can't logic be used?

logic stores values like a variable:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The alias statement requires net types (wire, tri, etc.). It cannot be used with variables such as logic, reg, int, or integer.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
shortint  <-- original type
    ↑
    |
 my_type  <-- alias (another name)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------code------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

module tb;

  wire [7:0] a;
  wire [7:0] num=7;

  alias a = num;
  initial $display("a=%0d num=%0d",a,num);

endmodule



